# Code owners for beava-dev/beava.
#
# Anyone listed here is automatically requested for review on PRs that
# touch a matching path. Used together with branch protection on `main`
# to require a code-owner approval before checks run + before merge.
#
# Format: <pattern> <owner>... — see
# https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-security/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

# Catch-all: every PR needs sign-off from the listed maintainers.
*                                @petrpan26

# Crates / Rust source — same maintainers, but listed explicitly so
# reviews land on the right people once the team grows.
/crates/                         @petrpan26
/Cargo.toml                      @petrpan26
/Cargo.lock                      @petrpan26

# Python SDK — gate alongside the wire format the binary speaks.
/python/                         @petrpan26

# CI / deploy infra — extra-careful path, owners-only edits in practice.
/.github/                        @petrpan26
/deploy/                         @petrpan26
/beava-website/deploy/           @petrpan26

